          <p class="">Some individuals can study in Canada without a study permit under the following specific circumstances:</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="">As a member of the armed forces of a designated state under the Visiting Forces Act.&nbsp;</p></li><li><p class="">If they are a family member or private staff of a properly accredited foreign representative in Canada for diplomatic or official duties.</p></li><li><p class="">If the course or program lasts for six months or less and is completed within the authorized stay period.&nbsp;</p></li><li><p class="">If they are an Indian, as recognized and defined in Canadian law.</p></li></ul>
        
      

      
        
      

