            Who doesn’t need a Provincial Attestation Letter (PAL)?
          </span>
          
            
              
                
                
              
            
          
        </button>
      </h4>
      
        
          <p class="">You are not required to obtain a Provincial Attestation Letter (PAL) when applying for a study permit if any of the following conditions apply to you: </p><p class=""> </p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="">You are applying to study in a preschool, primary school, or secondary school (up to grade 12). </p></li><li><p class="">You are applying to study in a master’s or doctoral degree program. </p></li><li><p class="">You have already entered Canada and meet one of the situations outlined in subsection 215(1) of the Immigration and Refugee Protection Regulations (IRPR), which may include being the family member of a foreign national residing in Canada under specific circumstances</p></li></ul>
        
      

      
        
      

    </li>
  
